The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Friday, January 07, 2005 

 Task force for Ganga Sagar 

 Calcutta, Jan. 6: A special task force comprising CID and intelligence branch officers has been set up for the four-day Ganga Sagar Mela beginning January 12.

 Police officers said the special measure was taken apprehending militant threats. 

 South 24-Parganas police chief S.. Gupta said: ?A platoon of IB officials and more than 50 CID officials under the command of a special superintendent will keep vigil on the fair ground.? 

 He added that more than 3,000 policemen, including 12 officers of the rank of superintendents and 100 women officers, will also be present.




